title: Small business revenue change
caption: Comparison between 2019 and subsequent years' daily small business revenue within 10 January, 2020 and 27 January, 2021 in Austin, TX.
insights: Between mid-March and mid-April, 2020 there was a mean steep decline of -43% in the small business revenue across all sectors compared to 2019.
The profile for transportation sector closely follows that of the mean profile.
The leisure and hospitality sector has had the lowest decline of -91%.
Since June, 2020, revenue in comparison to 2019 has remained relatively steady at an average of -36%.
